    "minides": "Tesla's first model in India — a fastback electric SUV imported as a CBU, offered in Standard RWD, Long Range RWD, and the six-seater long-wheelbase Model Y L AWD.",
    "description": "The Tesla Model Y marked Tesla's official entry into India in July 2025, launched as a fully imported (CBU) vehicle through experience centres in Mumbai, Delhi, Bengaluru, and Gurugram. It is offered in three configurations: a Standard RWD with a 60kWh battery and 500km WLTP range, a Long Range RWD with an 84.2kWh battery and up to 661km range, and the long-wheelbase six-seater Model Y L with dual-motor AWD, an 88kWh battery, and 681km range. All variants feature Tesla's minimalist cabin centred on a 15.4-inch touchscreen, a panoramic glass roof, an 8-inch rear-passenger screen, a 9-speaker sound system, and over-the-air software updates. Full Self-Driving (FSD) capability is offered as a Rs 6 lakh option, though full autonomy is not yet legally enabled in India. The Model Y has received a 5-star Euro NCAP safety rating and supports both AC and DC fast charging via Tesla's expanding Supercharger network."
  },
